records.descr: DE not competent to stand trial, case suspended

records.addlTxt: Defendant Benjamin F Notinokey in court with attorney Brett Lee Copeland.  Defendant Benjamin F Notinokey in custody.  William R. F. Ackell appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Benjamin F Notinokey appeared by video means. Defendant's family appears via zoom. Parties are stipulating to report. Court finds the defendant lacks substantial capacity to understand court proceedings or to assist in his own defense.  Court orders proceedings suspended.   Court ordered defendant committed to the Department of Health and Family Services for Institutional Care in order to restore competency within the statutory time frame with credit for 23 days time served.   Pursuant to Chief Judge Directive 22-04, parties are hereby notified that as of July 30, 2022, this case will be assigned to Branch 6, Judge Ellen Brostrom, in Room 608 of the Courthouse.
Public Defender Order Appointing Counsel, Filed.
Forensic evaluation ordered.  INITIAL APPEARANCE NOT HELD.  Trial court to address INITIAL APPEARANCE.

Defendant Benjamin F Notinokey in court with attorney Brett Lee Copeland.  Defendant Benjamin F Notinokey in custody.  Brittany Skye Kachingwe appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Benjamin F Notinokey appeared by video means with Attorney.  Court is advised by the defense there is reason to believe the defendant is not competent to proceed.  Pursuant to Sec. 971.14 (2) Wisconsin Statutes, Court found probable cause and ordered defendant examined by the Forensic Unit.  Order for Examination, signed and filed.   Defendant is advised this case is assigned to Judge Kies, Branch 45.   Court ordered defendant REMANDED into custody of Milwaukee County Sheriff's Department.  Commissioner tolls the time limits for the preliminary hearing.  Doctor's Report Return scheduled for June 7, 2022 at 08:30 am.

Order for Competency Examination, signed and filed.
